-[Tires Screeching]
-**And I shall hear**

558
00:41:06,997 --> 00:41:10,997
** Though soft
ye tread around me**

559
00:41:13,604 --> 00:41:17,604
**And all my grave**

560
00:41:18,275 --> 00:41:22,275
** Will warmer, sweeter be**

561
00:41:28,619 --> 00:41:31,383
** Then you will**

562
00:41:31,455 --> 00:41:35,455
**Bend**

563
00:41:37,528 --> 00:41:41,528
**And tell me
that you love me**

564
00:41:46,169 --> 00:41:50,169
**And I will sleep in peace**

565
00:41:51,942 --> 00:41:55,942
** Until you come**

566
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:03,550
** Tome****

567
00:42:07,658 --> 00:42:10,456
- Who's winning?
- We are, for the nonce.

568
00:42:10,527 --> 00:42:14,527
- What's the disposish?
- Last night, four to one. Dana
Cudahy went up with the house.

569
00:42:14,765 --> 00:42:16,960
- And theirs?
- One burned.

570
00:42:17,034 --> 00:42:18,797
- The other three?
- Lead.

571
00:42:18,869 --> 00:42:20,894
- Whose?
- Leo's.

572
00:42:20,971 --> 00:42:23,235
The old man's still
an artist with a Thompson.

573
00:42:23,307 --> 00:42:25,275
[Leo]
Yeah, do that.

574
00:42:25,342 --> 00:42:29,301
Well, find him, god damn it!
Go and see if he fell in the john.

575
00:42:30,747 --> 00:42:33,648
Son of a bitch. No chief.

576
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:37,084
- Who's mindin' the goddamn store?
-Cant raise O'Doole?

577
00:42:37,085 --> 00:42:38,685
No, nor the mayor either.

578
00:42:39,424 --> 00:42:43,424
- That's not good.
They're running.
- They wouldnt dare!

579
00:42:43,828 --> 00:42:46,524
I don't know, Leo.
I warned you not to
hit Caspar's club.

580
00:42:46,598 --> 00:42:49,396
- I'm still here, ain't I?
-Caspar's play hurt you anyway.

581
00:42:49,467 --> 00:42:51,958
That sorry son of a bitch
just slit his own throat.

582
00:42:52,036 --> 00:42:55,164
Listen to me, Leo.
Last night made you
look vulnerable.

583
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:58,676
You don't hold elected office
in this town. You run it
because people think you run it.

584
00:42:58,743 --> 00:43:01,507
Once they stop thinking it,
you stop running it.

585
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:05,015
Jesus, Tom. It sounds like
a bad break for me
I wasn't killed!

586
00:43:05,083 --> 00:43:08,143
I mean it, Leo.
Start taking Caspar seriously.

587
00:43:08,219 --> 00:43:12,219
I know, I know.
Retreat to win, give up Bernie.
That'll solve all our problems.

588
00:43:12,524 --> 00:43:14,583
Wont anymore, I'll grant you that.

589
00:43:14,659 --> 00:43:17,127
But going toe-to-toe
with a psychopath
will get you no where.

590
00:43:17,195 --> 00:43:19,891
It'll force people
to choose sides just when
you're looking shaky.

591
00:43:19,964 --> 00:43:23,263
- The hell I do!
- Then where's the mayor?

592
00:43:23,334 --> 00:43:25,564
Why aren't there
any police here?

593
00:43:25,637 --> 00:43:27,662
Why weren't there any police
At your place last night?

594
00:43:27,739 --> 00:43:30,333
- I didn't ask for any.
- I did.

595
00:43:30,408 --> 00:43:33,400
[ Laughs ]

596
00:43:33,478 --> 00:43:36,276
Mother hen, huh?
What's the matter, Tommy?

597
00:43:36,347 --> 00:43:39,874
- Dont you think
I can take care of myself?
- I know you can't.

598
00:43:39,951 --> 00:43:42,818
Here's the smart play, Leo.
You lay back, you give Bernie up,

599
00:43:42,887 --> 00:43:44,878
you let Caspar think
he's made his point.

600
00:43:44,956 --> 00:43:47,948
- Then you wait for him
to show a weakness.
- Please, Tom.

601
00:43:48,026 --> 00:43:50,256
You're sticking on Bernie.
You're sticking your neck out...

602
00:43:50,328 --> 00:43:53,263
for a guy who'd chop you off
at the heels if there
was two bits in it.

603
00:43:55,767 --> 00:43:58,463
[ Sighs ]
Tom,

604
00:43:58,536 --> 00:44:01,869
things aren't as, uh,
clear-cut as you make it.

605
00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:07,474
Bernie's--
Well, hell, you know
about me and Verna.

606
00:44:07,745 --> 00:44:11,613
Things now are, uh--

607
00:44:11,683 --> 00:44:15,449
Not that I haven't
been a gentleman, but--

608
00:44:17,522 --> 00:44:20,980
I plan to ask her
to marry me, Tom.

609
00:44:25,697 --> 00:44:29,064
I guess you think
that's a bonehead play.

610
00:44:33,371 --> 00:44:37,171
- You think she wants you to?
- How the hell do I know?

611
00:44:37,242 --> 00:44:39,938
I think she does.
Yeah, of course she does.

612
00:44:40,011 --> 00:44:43,879
I know you think different,
but, well, we just, uh--

613
00:44:43,948 --> 00:44:46,314
We just differ on that.

614
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:52,283
Leo, Caspar didn't kill Rug.

615
00:44:52,357 --> 00:44:56,123
- Course he did.
- No. Think about it
just this one time.

616
00:44:56,194 --> 00:44:58,219
- Who was Rug following?
- Huh?

617
00:44:58,296 --> 00:45:01,857
It needn't have been that
sinister. Strange man follows
her down a dark alleyway.

618
00:45:01,933 --> 00:45:04,333
- I told you she can
look after herself.
- Verna wouldnt panic,

619
00:45:04,402 --> 00:45:07,599
shoot someone just because
he was following her.

620
00:45:07,672 --> 00:45:11,472
Nah, it wouldn't have happened
like that, and if it had
she would have told me.

621
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:14,773
They pulled a .22 slug out of him.
A pop gun, Leo, a woman's gun.

622
00:45:14,846 --> 00:45:17,041
I know you don't
like her, Tom,

623
00:45:17,115 --> 00:45:20,107
but I trust Verna
as much as I trust you.

624
00:45:21,686 --> 00:45:23,620
Okay, Leo.

625
00:45:23,688 --> 00:45:25,986
Maybe it wasn't that innocent.

626
00:45:26,057 --> 00:45:29,720
Maybe Rug knew something
she didn't like him knowing
and wouldn't want you to know.

627
00:45:29,794 --> 00:45:33,457
Rug was following her.
Maybe he knew
where she was sleeping,

628
00:45:33,531 --> 00:45:35,465
and who with.

629
00:45:39,537 --> 00:45:42,028
Maybes don't make it so.

630
00:45:43,107 --> 00:45:45,098
There's more than maybes.

631
00:45:45,176 --> 00:45:48,737
You've trusted me before,
you've never lost anything
by it. Trust me on this.

632
00:45:51,549 --> 00:45:55,007
- This is too important.
- I don't ask much,
and I don't ask often.

633
00:45:55,086 --> 00:45:57,554
Trust me on this.

634
00:45:57,622 --> 00:46:00,887
- Tommy.
- Trust me on this,
or to hell with you.

635
00:46:03,528 --> 00:46:05,894
You don't mean that.

636
00:46:08,666 --> 00:46:10,600
She was with me...

637
00:46:10,668 --> 00:46:14,069
the night Rug
was following her,

638
00:46:14,138 --> 00:46:16,106
the night you dropped by.

639
00:46:17,675 --> 00:46:19,802
[ Scoffs ]

640
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:32,119
Oh.

641
00:47:24,175 --> 00:47:26,336
[ Grunts ]

642
00:47:38,756 --> 00:47:41,247
****[Irish Tenor, Indistinct]

643
00:47:50,535 --> 00:47:53,197
[Woman Screams]

644
00:48:17,962 --> 00:48:20,192
[ Screams ]

645
00:48:28,239 --> 00:48:31,003
Okay, Leo. Okay.
I'll throw him out.

646
00:48:33,144 --> 00:48:35,704
Yeah, do that.

647
00:48:36,781 --> 00:48:38,976
It's the kiss-off.

648
00:48:39,050 --> 00:48:42,383
If I never see him again,
it'll be soon enough.

649
00:48:45,656 --> 00:48:47,024
[Dialing Phone]

650
00:48:47,024 --> 00:48:48,286
[Dialing Phone]

651
00:48:52,730 --> 00:48:54,755
- Hello?
- Hello, Frankie.

652
00:48:54,832 --> 00:48:57,266
It's Tom.
How's the funky business?

653
00:48:58,569 --> 00:49:00,833
I've had worse.
Your ventilator mending?

654
00:49:00,905 --> 00:49:04,068
-[Knocking On Door]
- Tell Caspar it's forgotten.

655
00:49:04,142 --> 00:49:06,576
- I'd like to see him.
-[Knocking Continues]

656
00:49:08,212 --> 00:49:10,442
Ah. All right, let me know.

657
00:49:55,660 --> 00:49:59,619
It worked, whatever you did.

658
00:49:59,698 --> 00:50:03,134
Leo says we're quits.

659
00:50:03,201 --> 00:50:05,863
But you know I didn't have
anything to do with Rug.

660
00:50:05,937 --> 00:50:08,667
Maybe not.

661
00:50:08,740 --> 00:50:10,708
Anyway, that isn't
what soured him on you.

662
00:50:10,776 --> 00:50:13,108
Oh, you and me, huh?

663
00:50:14,880 --> 00:50:18,509
You always take
the long way around to get
what you want, dont you, Tom?

664
00:50:20,585 --> 00:50:23,019
You could have just asked.

665
00:50:25,924 --> 00:50:28,825
What did I want?

666
00:50:28,894 --> 00:50:31,522
Me.

667
00:50:51,383 --> 00:50:53,908
[ Rings ]

668
00:50:57,556 --> 00:51:00,286
Yeah?

669
00:51:00,358 --> 00:51:02,292
Yeah, yeah.

670
00:51:02,360 --> 00:51:04,692
When?

671
00:51:04,763 --> 00:51:06,697
Okay.

672
00:51:11,536 --> 00:51:14,300
You still up?

673
00:51:14,372 --> 00:51:16,602
Yeah.

674
00:51:20,412 --> 00:51:23,506
What are you chewin' over?

675
00:51:23,582 --> 00:51:25,812
Dream I had once.

676
00:51:27,719 --> 00:51:30,688
I was walking in the woods.
I don't know why.

677
00:51:32,257 --> 00:51:35,385
Wind came whippin'.
Blew me hat off.

678
00:51:37,362 --> 00:51:40,297
And you chased it, right?

679
00:51:40,365 --> 00:51:42,765
You ran and ran.

680
00:51:42,834 --> 00:51:45,997
You finally caught up to it.

681
00:51:46,071 --> 00:51:50,071
And you picked it up,
but it wasn't a hat anymore.

682
00:51:50,242 --> 00:51:54,201
It had changed into something else,
something wonderful.

683
00:51:54,279 --> 00:51:57,112
No, it stayed a hat.

684
00:51:57,182 --> 00:51:59,673
And no, I didn't chase it.

685
00:52:01,019 --> 00:52:04,853
Nothing more foolish
than a man chasin' his hat.

686
00:52:04,923 --> 00:52:07,153
Where are you going?

687
00:52:07,225 --> 00:52:09,989
Just have to do a few things.

688
00:52:10,061 --> 00:52:13,519
- You and Leo might still
be able to patch things up.
- Me and Leo are finished.

689
00:52:13,598 --> 00:52:17,090
-Nothing's gonna change that.
- You never know.

690
00:52:17,168 --> 00:52:20,968
- He's got a big heart.
- We're quits as far as I'm
concerned, never mind him.

691
00:52:21,039 --> 00:52:25,039
And if Leo did want me back,
he's an even bigger sap
than I thought.

692
00:52:25,377 --> 00:52:27,868
Then why don't we just
pick up and leave town?

693
00:52:27,946 --> 00:52:30,813
There's nothing keeping you here.

694
00:52:30,882 --> 00:52:32,816
I know there's nothing keeping me.

695
00:52:32,884 --> 00:52:36,217
- What about Bernie?
- He could go with us.

696
00:52:37,455 --> 00:52:39,616
You, me and Bernie?
Where would we go, Verna?

697
00:52:39,691 --> 00:52:41,625
Niagara Falls?

698
00:52:41,693 --> 00:52:43,627
Why do you hate him?

699
00:52:43,695 --> 00:52:45,629
- I don't hate anyone.
-Or like any one.

700
00:52:50,702 --> 00:52:52,897
Where is Bernie?

701
00:52:52,971 --> 00:52:55,462
- Why?
- Leo can't protect him anymore.

702
00:52:55,540 --> 00:52:58,998
I oughta tell him to skip.

703
00:52:59,077 --> 00:53:01,011
The Royale, room 302.

704
00:53:06,284 --> 00:53:09,913
I guess we both
double-crossed Leo, huh?

705
00:53:09,988 --> 00:53:11,922
There's no gettin' around that.

706
00:53:13,058 --> 00:53:15,856
I guess he's well rid
of both of us.

707
00:53:15,927 --> 00:53:19,927
The two of us, we're about
bad enough to deserve each other.

708
00:53:23,802 --> 00:53:25,736
Are we?

709
00:53:27,839 --> 00:53:30,740
We're a couple of heels, Tom.

710
00:53:30,809 --> 00:53:33,505
Yes, we are.

711
00:53:33,678 --> 00:53:37,678
[Caspar]So he says,
Screw him. Give him a dollar.
This was my idea. 

712
00:53:38,149 --> 00:53:41,880
[Laughing]
Hello, Tom.

713
00:53:41,953 --> 00:53:45,184
Uh, you know O'Doole
and the mayor.

714
00:53:45,256 --> 00:53:48,555
- Hello, boys.
- Tom's a big booster.
Always has been.

715
00:53:48,626 --> 00:53:52,626
That's fine, that's fine.
Well, Tom and I got
the proverbial fat to chew.

716
00:53:52,797 --> 00:53:55,595
-Just let us know
if you need anything.
- Yeah. Happy days.

717
00:53:55,667 --> 00:53:58,727
Have a seat, kid.
Yeah, that's it.

718
00:53:58,803 --> 00:54:02,136
So, you had enough time
to think about things?

719
00:54:02,207 --> 00:54:06,207
- Yeah, well, uh,
circumstances have changed.
- Don't I know it.

720
00:54:06,378 --> 00:54:09,472
Last night I know the Dane
was disappointed
the bulls showed up...

721
00:54:09,547 --> 00:54:12,209
before Frankie and Tic-Tac
really pinned your ears back,

722
00:54:12,283 --> 00:54:16,283
but I said, Relax, Eddie.
I got a feeling about this kid.

723
00:54:16,821 --> 00:54:20,821
The kid and Leo
are gonna go bust-o.
Matter of time.

724
00:54:21,126 --> 00:54:23,822
I said, The kid
is too smart for Leo.
That's what I said.

725
00:54:23,895 --> 00:54:26,955
Like a psychic.
Ask the Dane if I did.
Like a goddamn psychic.

726
00:54:27,032 --> 00:54:29,523
-Go ahead, ask him.
- You vouch for that
psychic business?

727
00:54:29,601 --> 00:54:32,161
- That's right, smart guy.
-I know you knew...

728
00:54:32,237 --> 00:54:35,263
protecting the shmatte
was a dumb idea.

729
00:54:35,340 --> 00:54:39,037
I know you've been wise
to all of Leo's dumb ideas lately.

730
00:54:39,110 --> 00:54:41,237
Only a matter of time-- bust-o.

731
00:54:41,312 --> 00:54:44,475
