your play on Leo,
I can only be so grateful.

733
00:54:48,153 --> 00:54:52,153
- Oh, that's real brave coming
from Little Miss Punching Bag.
- Okay, Eddie.

734
00:54:52,490 --> 00:54:55,755
- Friends now, huh?
- Nuts.

735
00:54:57,429 --> 00:54:59,363
So, I guess you'll be
looking for a job, eh, kid?

736
00:54:59,431 --> 00:55:02,093
I might be.

737
00:55:02,167 --> 00:55:04,192
You got references?
You been to college?

738
00:55:04,269 --> 00:55:07,864
We only take eggs
what's been to college.
Ain't that right, Dane?

739
00:55:07,939 --> 00:55:10,669
[ Laughs ]

740
00:55:10,742 --> 00:55:14,007
I'm joking, of course.
We all know you could be
useful to us,

741
00:55:14,079 --> 00:55:16,013
a smart kid such as yourself.

742
00:55:16,081 --> 00:55:19,881
The man who walks behind the man,
who whispers in his ear.

743
00:55:19,951 --> 00:55:23,614
- I guess you could be
useful in spades.
- Yeah, I can do plenty for you.

744
00:55:23,688 --> 00:55:27,688
- Can you get Leo off me?
- I'm tellin' you
not to worry about Leo.

745
00:55:28,193 --> 00:55:30,127
- We got plans for him.
- Oh, yeah?

746
00:55:30,195 --> 00:55:33,028
- Like what?
- Not so fast there, kaputnik.

747
00:55:33,098 --> 00:55:35,623
I-I think what the Dane
is trying to say is,

748
00:55:35,700 --> 00:55:37,634
there'll be time
to talk about that.

749
00:55:37,702 --> 00:55:40,068
We can table that
for a later date.

750
00:55:41,539 --> 00:55:45,539
See, last time we jawed,
you gave me the high hat.

751
00:55:46,211 --> 00:55:48,736
I guess I'm sayin'...

752
00:55:48,813 --> 00:55:52,340
you gotta put something
on the table first.

753
00:55:52,417 --> 00:55:55,147
- Ante up.
- Fair enough. Where do we start?

754
00:55:55,220 --> 00:55:58,747
Hear that, Dane? All business.
I told you he was a good kid.

755
00:55:58,823 --> 00:56:01,018
Where do we start?
All business.

756
00:56:01,092 --> 00:56:04,186
Well, we can start, for instance,
with the shmatte.

757
00:56:04,262 --> 00:56:06,230
Like, where's the shmatte?
You could may be tell us that.

758
00:56:06,297 --> 00:56:10,297
The Royale, room 302.
And you might find Mink with him.

759
00:56:10,502 --> 00:56:12,470
[Eddie]
The hell you say.

760
00:56:12,537 --> 00:56:14,664
[Tom]
Sure. Bernie and Mink
are cozy as lice.

761
00:56:14,739 --> 00:56:18,038
- And it ain't just business.
- This guy is lying.

762
00:56:18,109 --> 00:56:20,043
- Why would I?
- This guy is wrong.

763
00:56:20,044 --> 00:56:23,744
This guy is all wrong.
Mink is clean and this clown
is a smart guy.

764
00:56:27,059 --> 00:56:29,084
It's easy enough to find out,
ain't it?

765
00:56:30,329 --> 00:56:34,329
You find Mink,
you bring him back here.

766
00:56:36,468 --> 00:56:40,427
Go to the car.
I'm gonna send Frankie and
Tic-Tac with you to the Royale.

767
00:56:40,506 --> 00:56:42,770
If Bernies there,

768
00:56:42,841 --> 00:56:45,207
Frankie and Tic-Tac'll
take care of him.

769
00:56:45,277 --> 00:56:47,677
And if hes not there?

770
00:56:47,746 --> 00:56:51,182
I'll sit facing the corner
in a funny hat.

771
00:56:52,818 --> 00:56:55,514
- [ Screams ]
- Get your little hebe ass
in the car.

772
00:56:55,587 --> 00:56:57,680
