that you bumped
the shmatte and lit out.

890
01:04:32,560 --> 01:04:34,858
Lousy son of a bitch.

891
01:04:36,564 --> 01:04:40,091
- I told you so.
- What?

892
01:04:40,167 --> 01:04:42,101
[ Laughs ]

893
01:04:42,169 --> 01:04:46,037
You got a lip on you.
That's all right.

894
01:04:46,106 --> 01:04:49,200
I don't generally care for it,
but that's all right.

895
01:04:50,544 --> 01:04:53,479
You was a good sport
to bump the shmatte.

896
01:04:54,548 --> 01:04:56,641
How do you know
Mink skipped?

897
01:04:56,717 --> 01:04:59,550
- Because the Dane can't find him.
- So he says.

898
01:04:59,620 --> 01:05:03,620
- Meaning what exactly?
-Maybe nothing.

899
01:05:03,791 --> 01:05:07,791
I didn't give it much thought,
'cause a guy'll say anything
when his number is up.

900
01:05:07,928 --> 01:05:10,658
But, uh,just before
I bumped Bernie,

901
01:05:10,731 --> 01:05:13,825
he swore tome
that Eddie Dane and Mink
were setting him up--

902
01:05:13,901 --> 01:05:16,836
that they were the ones
who sold out your fix.

903
01:05:25,412 --> 01:05:27,346
Well, uh--

904
01:05:27,414 --> 01:05:29,746
Well, like you say, uh,
a guy'll say anything.

905
01:05:29,817 --> 01:05:32,251
So why isn't
Eddie Dane here?

906
01:05:34,021 --> 01:05:36,649
Well, he don't
care for you, kid.

907
01:05:37,725 --> 01:05:40,660
Maybe it's only fair to tell you.

908
01:05:40,728 --> 01:05:44,220
After you left us,
he tried to sell me
on a double-cross.

909
01:05:44,298 --> 01:05:47,199
He says tome,
why don't we double-cross you
and give you the bump...

910
01:05:47,268 --> 01:05:49,202
after we get the shmatte.

911
01:05:49,270 --> 01:05:53,263
Well, I figure a deal's a deal.
You're square with me.

912
01:05:53,340 --> 01:05:57,340
You bump the shmatte,
I hold up my end.
It's a question of ethics.

913
01:05:58,145 --> 01:06:02,145
Everything above board so
everybody knows who's a friend,
whos an enemy.

914
01:06:03,817 --> 01:06:07,014
So the Dane doesn't like you,
but he wouldn't cross me.

915
01:06:07,087 --> 01:06:09,021
We go back.

916
01:06:10,925 --> 01:06:14,925
Of course there's always
that wild card when,
uh, love is involved.

917
01:06:18,766 --> 01:06:21,200
I know Mink
is Eddie Dane's boy.

918
01:06:23,203 --> 01:06:25,763
Still, I--
I don't make it that way.

919
01:06:27,608 --> 01:06:30,975
- Then there's nothing
to worry about.
- Yeah.

920
01:06:31,045 --> 01:06:35,045
Papa, Papa, I got a prize
from the sister! Papa, Papa,
I got a prize from the sister!

921
01:06:35,449 --> 01:06:38,850
- Papa, Papa, I got a prize
from the sister!
- Yeah. Just a minute.

922
01:06:38,919 --> 01:06:41,114
- Of course, then, there's
no reason-- Shut up!
- Papa, Papa, I got--

923
01:06:41,188 --> 01:06:44,589
You take a page
out of this guy's book.

924
01:06:44,658 --> 01:06:48,658
- A little less you talk,
a little more you think!
- [ Bawling ]

925
01:06:50,965 --> 01:06:53,331
Kids. You gotta be firm.

926
01:06:53,400 --> 01:06:57,400
Anyways, there's no reason
not to check things out.

927
01:06:58,205 --> 01:07:01,606
If Mink is around,
I want you to find him.
He can tell us what's what.

928
01:07:01,675 --> 01:07:04,735
What's the matter?
Somebody hit you?

929
01:07:04,812 --> 01:07:07,645
What's the matter?
Aren't we friends anymore?

930
01:07:07,715 --> 01:07:10,650
If you find him,
I wanna talk to him alone.

931
01:07:10,718 --> 01:07:13,346
That's the way you get
the straight dope--man to man.

932
01:07:13,420 --> 01:07:17,117
Just me, Mink...
and my friend Roscoe.

933
01:07:17,191 --> 01:07:19,853
You understand
what I'm saying?

934
01:07:19,927 --> 01:07:22,361
- It ain't complicated.
- [Boy Howling]

935
01:07:33,073 --> 01:07:37,073
You should leave town
for a few days. Things are
gonna heat up around here.

936
01:07:37,611 --> 01:07:40,045
Go to the Palisades.
I'll join you soon as I'm done.

937
01:07:40,114 --> 01:07:43,049
I can't find Bernie.
Did you find him?

938
01:07:44,351 --> 01:07:46,285
Yeah.

939
01:07:46,353 --> 01:07:48,548
Is he leaving?

940
01:07:48,622 --> 01:07:52,622
He, uh-- He left.

941
01:07:53,060 --> 01:07:55,654
- He say where to?
- He didn't say.

942
01:07:55,729 --> 01:07:57,924
- You--
- Thanks.

943
01:08:11,578 --> 01:08:14,911
-[Dane] What's that
potato-eater up to?
- [Thug]Beats me.

944
01:08:14,982 --> 01:08:17,450
- That's Bernie's sister, ain't it?
- Beats me.

945
01:08:17,518 --> 01:08:19,918
- What's he seeing her for?
- Beats me. Maybe--

946
01:08:19,987 --> 01:08:23,753
Shut up. Get lost.

947
01:08:23,824 --> 01:08:26,384
I'll see where
the twist fops.

948
01:08:27,594 --> 01:08:31,086
You know who I am?

949
01:08:31,165 --> 01:08:33,827
Yeah, Johnny Caspar's shadow.
What, did he stay in bed today?

950
01:08:33,901 --> 01:08:37,894
Jesus. I open my mouth,
the whole world turns smart.

951
01:08:37,971 --> 01:08:41,498
- You're Leo's twist, right?
- Me and Leo are through.

952
01:08:41,575 --> 01:08:44,339
Yeah?
So youre sluttin' around
with Tom now, huh?

953
01:08:44,411 --> 01:08:47,175
You get outta here.

954
01:08:47,247 --> 01:08:49,545
Okay. See you later.

955
01:08:51,618 --> 01:08:54,052
Before I go,
what's your boyfriend up to?

956
01:08:54,121 --> 01:08:56,248
- Nothing I know about.
- Yeah?

957
01:08:56,323 --> 01:08:58,416
That doesn't
figure for me--

958
01:08:58,492 --> 01:09:01,620
you dumpin' Leo for the guy
who put a bullet in your brother.

959
01:09:05,599 --> 01:09:09,599
He didn't tell you. Aww.

960
01:09:10,270 --> 01:09:12,204
Spin her, Eddie.

961
01:09:13,307 --> 01:09:15,775
Ooh!

962
01:09:24,518 --> 01:09:26,884
[ Straining ]

963
01:09:31,859 --> 01:09:35,859
- You Leo's?
- Yeah. He wanted her
looked-out for.

964
01:09:36,096 --> 01:09:40,096
Well, you did a bang-up job.
I'll be sure to tell him.

965
01:09:40,367 --> 01:09:44,367
- Where's Leo?
- If I tell you, how do I know
you won't kill me?

966
01:09:44,505 --> 01:09:48,505
Because if you told me and I
killed you and you were lying,
I wouldn't get to kill you then.

967
01:09:49,743 --> 01:09:52,439
- Where's Leo?
- He's moving around.

968
01:09:52,513 --> 01:09:56,513
- He's getting his mob together
tomorrow at Whiskey Nick's.
- You sure?

969
01:09:56,683 --> 01:09:58,617
Check it. It's gold.

970
01:09:58,685 --> 01:10:02,280
You know what, yegg?
I believe you.

971
01:10:24,968 --> 01:10:26,993
Go ahead and run, sweetie.

972
01:10:27,070 --> 01:10:30,562
I'll track down
all of you whores.

973
01:10:35,511 --> 01:10:37,445
[Knocking]

974
01:10:43,453 --> 01:10:45,387
[Doorknob Rattling]

975
01:10:55,999 --> 01:10:57,933
[Door Opens]

976
01:11:00,903 --> 01:11:02,837
[Door Closes]

977
01:11:30,133 --> 01:11:33,899
Hello, Bernie. Come on in.
Make your self at home.

978
01:11:33,970 --> 01:11:36,962
Hello, Tom.

979
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:40,806
I thought I'd do that,
since you didn't seem to be in.

980
01:11:40,877 --> 01:11:44,877
Figured it was a bad idea
to wait in the hall, seeing
as I'm supposed to be dead.

981
01:11:48,151 --> 01:11:50,585
How'd you know it was me?

982
01:11:50,654 --> 01:11:53,145
You're the only one I know
who'd knock and then break in.

983
01:11:53,223 --> 01:11:55,214
Your other friends
wouldn't break in?

984
01:11:55,292 --> 01:11:58,489
My other friends
want to kill me,
so they wouldn't knock.

985
01:11:58,562 --> 01:12:00,996
What's on your mind. Bernie?

986
01:12:03,400 --> 01:12:05,800
Things.

987
01:12:05,869 --> 01:12:09,869
I guess you must be angry.
I'm supposed to be
gone far away.

988
01:12:11,408 --> 01:12:14,502
I guess it seems sort of
irresponsible, my being here.

989
01:12:17,013 --> 01:12:20,505
And I was gonna leave.
Honest, I was.

990
01:12:20,584 --> 01:12:22,518
But then I started thinking...

991
01:12:22,586 --> 01:12:25,453
if I stuck around,
that would not be good for you.

992
01:12:25,522 --> 01:12:28,252
Then I started
thinking that--

993
01:12:28,325 --> 01:12:30,759
that might not
be bad for me.

994
01:12:31,995 --> 01:12:33,929
[Chuckles]

995
01:12:33,997 --> 01:12:36,727
You didn't see
the play you gave me.

996
01:12:36,800 --> 01:12:39,064
I mean, what am I gonna do?

997
01:12:39,135 --> 01:12:42,070
If I leave, I got nothing.

998
01:12:42,138 --> 01:12:44,868
No money, no friends, nothing.

999
01:12:44,941 --> 01:12:47,102
If I stay, I got you.

1000
01:12:47,177 --> 01:12:51,177
Anyone finds out I'm alive,
you're dead, so...

1001
01:12:53,850 --> 01:12:55,875
I got-- I got you, Tommy.

1002
01:12:58,388 --> 01:13:01,789
What's the matter?
You got nothing
to crack wise about?

1003
01:13:01,858 --> 01:13:04,292
Bernie ain't
so funny anymore?

1004
01:13:07,564 --> 01:13:10,499
I guess I made kind of
a fool of my self out there...

1005
01:13:12,702 --> 01:13:15,193
bawling away like a twist.

1006
01:13:15,271 --> 01:13:17,705
I guess--

1007
01:13:17,774 --> 01:13:19,708
I guess I turned yellow.

1008
01:13:19,776 --> 01:13:23,473
- You didn't tell anyone
about that?
- No.

1009
01:13:23,546 --> 01:13:25,741
Of course,
you know about it.

1010
01:13:29,686 --> 01:13:31,847
It's a painful memory...

1011
01:13:33,757 --> 01:13:37,757
and I can't help remembering
that you put the finger on me,

1012
01:13:38,662 --> 01:13:41,756
and you took me out there
to whack me.

1013
01:13:41,831 --> 01:13:45,460
I know... you didn't.
I know.

1014
01:13:45,535 --> 01:13:49,335
- You didn't shoot me, but--
- But what have I done
for you lately?

1015
01:13:49,406 --> 01:13:51,465
Don't smart me.

1016
01:13:53,009 --> 01:13:55,443
See, I want
to watch you squirm.

1017
01:13:57,013 --> 01:13:59,447
I want to see you
sweat a little.

1018
01:14:01,351 --> 01:14:03,444
And when you smart me...

1019
01:14:04,988 --> 01:14:07,422
it ruins it.

1020
01:14:17,267 --> 01:14:19,701
There's one other thing I want.

1021
01:14:21,604 --> 01:14:24,368
I want to see Johnny Caspar
cold and stiff.

1022
01:14:24,441 --> 01:14:27,842
That's what youll do
for your friend Bernie.

1023
01:14:30,947 --> 01:14:34,212
In the meantime,
I'll stay out of sight.

1024
01:14:34,284 --> 01:14:37,720
But if Caspar ain't stiff
in a couple of days...

1025
01:14:37,787 --> 01:14:39,880
I start eating
in restaurants.

1026
01:14:53,770 --> 01:14:56,000
Oof!.

1027
01:14:59,843 --> 01:15:02,676
Uuh!

1028
01:15:02,746 --> 01:15:04,839
You make me laugh, Tommy.

1029
01:15:04,914 --> 01:15:08,475
You're gonna catch cold.
Then you're no good to me.

1030
01:15:08,551 --> 01:15:11,486
What were you gonna do
if you caught me?

1031
01:15:11,554 --> 01:15:14,990
Id just squirt a few,
and then you'd let me go again.

1032
01:15:21,998 --> 01:15:25,331
Hello, Tad.
How's the club holding up?

1033
01:15:25,401 --> 01:15:29,098
We're managing to squeak by
without you.
Got Lazarre's money?

1034
01:15:29,172 --> 01:15:32,266
- No.
- You're not supposed to be here
since you turned rat.

1035
01:15:32,342 --> 01:15:34,902
Relax, Tad.
Leo isn't around, is he?

1036
01:15:34,978 --> 01:15:38,978
Last couple of days you booked
any heavy bets on a long shot
at Saturday's fights?

1037
01:15:39,149 --> 01:15:41,208
Why the hell
should I tell you?

1038
01:15:41,284 --> 01:15:45,152
The truth is, Tad,
no reason on Earth.

1039
01:15:47,724 --> 01:15:49,715
Saturday's fights?

1040
01:15:49,793 --> 01:15:53,752
Drop Johnson put two grand
on one yesterday--

1041
01:15:53,830 --> 01:15:57,266
on Sailor Reese,
an under card bum.

1042
01:15:57,333 --> 01:16:00,393
Drop Johnson.
He play your book much?

1043
01:16:00,470 --> 01:16:03,769
- Are you kidding? I didn't
even know he could count.
- [Woman Screams]

1044
01:16:03,840 --> 01:16:06,104
Jesus. You bring them with you?

1045
01:16:06,176 --> 01:16:09,577
Hello, Brian.
Still fighting the good fight?

1046
01:16:09,646 --> 01:16:11,944
Hello, Tom.
Neither rain nor wind nor snow.

1047
01:16:12,015 --> 01:16:14,108
That's the mailman. O'Doole here?

1048
01:16:20,590 --> 01:16:23,525
Hello, O'Doole.
You don't look happy.

1049
01:16:23,593 --> 01:16:25,720
Look at this mess.

1050
01:16:25,795 --> 01:16:29,094
Guttin' the golden calf again.
I don't know whether to laugh or cry.

1051
01:16:29,165 --> 01:16:32,862
Yeah, it's awful confusing.
You know a yegg
named Drop Johnson?

1052
01:16:32,936 --> 01:16:35,734
- We spanked him
a couple of times.
- Where does he flop?

1053
01:16:35,805 --> 01:16:38,000
- Terminal Hotel, Bay Street.
- [Gunshot]

1054
01:16:38,074 --> 01:16:42,074
Jesus!
Look, don't nobody ask me since
I'm just the chief around here,

1055
01:16:42,545 --> 01:16:44,638
but I'll tell you my opinion.

1056
01:16:44,714 --> 01:16:48,714
Caspar is just as crazy as Leo,
and an eye-tie
into the bargain.

1057
01:16:49,152 --> 01:16:52,315
What's the matter, O'Doole?
Doesn't anything ever suit you?

1058
01:17:02,532 --> 01:17:05,330
Hop in, Tom.
We been lookin' for you.

1059
01:17:05,401 --> 01:17:07,801
- I'm busy.
- Hop in anyway.

1060
01:17:07,871 --> 01:17:11,136
You can't hijack me, Tic-Tac.
We're on the same side now.

1061
01:17:11,207 --> 01:17:14,005
Or didnt you get
that far in school?

1062
01:17:23,353 --> 01:17:25,218
How'd you get the fat lip?

1063
01:17:25,288 --> 01:17:29,288
- Old war wound.
Acts up around morons.
- Very smart.

1064
01:17:29,726 --> 01:17:32,854
What were you doing
at the club, talking
things over with Leo?

1065
01:17:32,929 --> 01:17:35,864
Don't think so hard, Eddie.
You might sprain something.

1066
01:17:35,932 --> 01:17:38,662
You are so goddamn smart.

1067
01:17:38,735 --> 01:17:40,669
Except you ain't.

1068
01:17:40,737 --> 01:17:43,706
I get you, smart guy.
I know what you are.

1069
01:17:43,773 --> 01:17:45,707
Straight as a corkscrew.

1070
01:17:45,775 --> 01:17:47,709
Mr. Inside Out-ski,

1071
01:17:47,777 --> 01:17:51,777
like some goddamn Bolshevik
picking up his orders
from Yegg Central.

1072
01:17:51,981 --> 01:17:54,074
You think youre
so goddamn smart.

1073
01:17:54,150 --> 01:17:56,345
You join up Johnny Caspar,

1074
01:17:56,419 --> 01:17:58,512
you bump Bernie Bernbaum.

1075
01:17:59,722 --> 01:18:03,123
Up is down. Black is white.

1076
01:18:04,460 --> 01:18:07,520
Well, I think youre half smart.

1077
01:18:07,597 --> 01:18:10,191
I think you were straight
with your frail,

1078
01:18:10,266 --> 01:18:12,860
I think you were queer
with Johnny Caspar...

1079
01:18:12,936 --> 01:18:16,936
and I think youd sooner
join a ladies' league
than gun a guy down.

1080
01:18:17,206 --> 01:18:21,206
Then I hear from these
two geniuses they never even
saw this rub-out take place.

1081
01:18:21,610 --> 01:18:24,610
- Boss said to have him do it.
He didn't say nothing about--
- Shut up!

1082
01:18:25,624 --> 01:18:28,787
Or maybe you still got
too many teeth.

1083
01:18:31,396 --> 01:18:35,396
Everyone is so goddamn smart.

1084
01:18:35,667 --> 01:18:39,433
Well, we'll go out
to Miller's Crossing...

1085
01:18:39,504 --> 01:18:42,439
and we'll see who's smart.

1086
01:18:46,812 --> 01:18:49,337
****[Frankie Singing
In Italian]

1087
01:19:06,598 --> 01:19:10,598
You understand if we don't
find a stiff out here,
we leave a fresh one.

1088
01:19:27,819 --> 01:19:30,754
Where are your friends
when you need 'em, huh?

1089
01:19:31,990 --> 01:19:34,424
Where's Leo now?

1090
01:19:36,395 --> 01:19:38,829
Hey, Tic-Tac!

1091
01:19:38,897 --> 01:19:42,731
You ever notice how
the snappy dialogue dries up...

1092
01:19:42,801 --> 01:19:45,361
once a guy starts
soiling his union suit?

1093
01:19:45,437 --> 01:19:47,871
[ Chuckling ]

1094
01:19:52,778 --> 01:19:54,871
****[Continues]

1095
01:20:01,620 --> 01:20:03,588
** [ Stops ]

1096
01:20:06,324 --> 01:20:08,485
** [ Resumes ]

1097
01:20:20,972 --> 01:20:23,668
[Retching]

1098
01:20:29,114 --> 01:20:33,114
Okay. There's nothing out here.

1099
01:20:33,452 --> 01:20:37,452
****[Stops]

1100
01:20:38,323 --> 01:20:42,020
****[Resumes]

1101
01:20:46,431 --> 01:20:50,431
- [ Groans ]
- Think about this... smart guy.

1102
01:20:51,303 --> 01:20:54,204
[Tic-Tac]
It's hanky time.

1103
01:20:56,174 --> 01:20:58,904
[ Coughing ]

1104
01:20:58,977 --> 01:21:02,310
- ** [ Stops ]
- Birds have been at him.

1105
01:21:02,380 --> 01:21:04,871
Jesus Christ.

1106
01:21:04,950 --> 01:21:07,441
[ Grunts ]

1107
01:21:16,728 --> 01:21:19,060
[ Coughing Continues ]

1108
01:21:29,508 --> 01:21:33,444
Told you
to put one in his brain,
not in his stinkin' face!

1109
01:21:33,512 --> 01:21:35,605
[WheezingLaughter]

1110
01:21:37,449 --> 01:21:41,180
[ Frankie ]
I told you, Dane.
We heard two shots.

1111
01:21:48,326 --> 01:21:50,658
[Man, Woman Arguing,
Indistinct]

1112
01:22:08,747 --> 01:22:10,840
Hello, Drop.

1113
01:22:14,553 --> 01:22:16,987
How are the Katzen jammers?

1114
01:22:17,055 --> 01:22:19,785
Hello, Tom. What's the rumpus?

1115
01:22:21,159 --> 01:22:23,354
Had any visitors?

1116
01:22:23,428 --> 01:22:25,521
Uhh, no.

1117
01:22:25,597 --> 01:22:27,531
Not ever, Drop?

1118
01:22:27,599 --> 01:22:29,590
Not lately.

1119
01:22:29,668 --> 01:22:32,228
Then you must be happy to see me.

1120
01:22:35,373 --> 01:22:37,307
So, uh...

1121
01:22:37,375 --> 01:22:41,243
you didn't see Bernie Bernbaum
before he was shown across.

1122
01:22:41,313 --> 01:22:43,338
Uh, no.

1123
01:22:43,415 --> 01:22:45,474
Seen him since?

1124
01:22:47,586 --> 01:22:49,918
One last question, Drop.

1125
01:22:49,988 --> 01:22:53,988
You got a lot of money
on tomorrow's fight.

1126
01:22:54,659 --> 01:22:58,659
That your bet, or, uh...
you placing it for a friend?

1127
01:22:58,897 --> 01:23:00,831
No, no, no, it's my bet.

1128
01:23:00,899 --> 01:23:04,899
- I just have a good feeling
about that fight.
- A good feeling, huh?

1129
01:23:05,670 --> 01:23:08,298
When did a feeling
return to your head?

1130
01:23:08,373 --> 01:23:11,001
You've outgrown that one.

1131
01:23:11,076 --> 01:23:13,271
Must be all the thinking
you been doing.

1132
01:23:13,345 --> 01:23:16,439
Tell Bernie something's come up,
he has to get in touch.

1133
01:23:16,514 --> 01:23:19,506
There'll be nothing stirring
till I talk to him.

1134
01:23:19,584 --> 01:23:19,917
****[Male Irish Tenor,
Indistinct]

1135
01:23:19,918 --> 01:23:21,681
****[Male Irish Tenor,
Indistinct]

1136
01:23:51,850 --> 01:23:55,850
All right, anyone left in there,
come on out grabbing air.
You know the drill.

1137
01:24:07,832 --> 01:24:09,766
[Coughs]

1138
01:24:12,871 --> 01:24:15,635
Aah!

1139
01:24:17,375 --> 01:24:20,344
[Laughter]

1140
01:24:25,350 --> 01:24:27,284
[Machine Gun Firing]

1141
01:24:58,383 --> 01:25:01,318
Hello, Tom.
Where you been hiding?

1142
01:25:01,386 --> 01:25:03,650
Hither and yon.
Is the mayor in?

1143
01:25:03,722 --> 01:25:06,213
- He's with Mr. Caspar.
- That's who I'm looking for.

1144
01:25:06,291 --> 01:25:09,488
- Scare me up some gargle, will you?
- Sure. I'll announce you.

1145
01:25:09,561 --> 01:25:12,325
Don't bother. I'm well-liked.

1146
01:25:13,998 --> 01:25:17,161
[Mayor]I can't do it.
I'll look ridiculous.
It simply isn't done.

1147
01:25:17,235 --> 01:25:20,227
-Assistants, maybe.
- For a mayor, you don't hear so hot.

1148
01:25:20,305 --> 01:25:23,331
I said head.
Head of the assessor's office.

1149
01:25:23,408 --> 01:25:27,408
- But there are two of them.
- I can count. Co-heads.

1150
01:25:27,645 --> 01:25:30,739
Johnny, needless to say,
this office will do
anything in its power...

1151
01:25:30,815 --> 01:25:33,409
to assist you and your cousins.

1152
01:25:35,290 --> 01:25:37,315
We did it for Leo, of course,
on countless occasions.

1153
01:25:37,392 --> 01:25:41,351
Damn right.
Had every potato-eater from
County Cork on the public tit.

1154
01:25:41,430 --> 01:25:43,864
But there's a way we do things,

1155
01:25:43,932 --> 01:25:47,095
hallowed by usage
and consecrated by time.

1156
01:25:47,169 --> 01:25:51,169
- When we put people on the pad
when Leo was running things--
- Leo ain't runnin' things!

1157
01:25:52,307 --> 01:25:56,307
I ain't interested
in ancient history!
I'm runnin' things now!

1158
01:25:56,779 --> 01:25:59,270
Nobody can appreciate it
more than I.

1159
01:25:59,348 --> 01:26:01,646
I can give them jobs.
I can give them good jobs.

1160
01:26:01,717 --> 01:26:04,880
I can even give them jobs
where they wont have
to perform any work,

1161
01:26:04,953 --> 01:26:07,786
where their lack of English
will be no impediment, but I can't--

1162
01:26:07,856 --> 01:26:10,120
What is this, the high hat?

1163
01:26:10,192 --> 01:26:14,192
Tom, can you explain it to him?
I can put them in public works,
but I can't--

1164
01:26:15,497 --> 01:26:17,431
You can do whatever
the hell Caspar tells you.

1165
01:26:17,499 --> 01:26:19,967
I don't remember
all this double talk
when Leo gave you an order.

1166
01:26:20,035 --> 01:26:24,035
- Tom. Jesus!
- Stop whimpering
and do as you're told.

1167
01:26:24,373 --> 01:26:27,570
- You can start
by gettin' out of here.
-Johnny, it's my office.

1168
01:26:27,643 --> 01:26:31,643
Get out of here!
Take it on the heel and toe
before I whack you one!

1169
01:26:34,883 --> 01:26:37,283
- You two beat it.
- [ Snaps Fingers ]

1170
01:26:37,352 --> 01:26:41,352
- [ Italian ]
- Yeah, go and keep
the mayor company.

1171
01:26:41,557 --> 01:26:44,617
I'll take care
of ya's later.

1172
01:26:51,834 --> 01:26:54,029
[ Sighs ]

1173
01:26:54,102 --> 01:26:57,037
- Runnin' things--
it ain't all gravy.
-[Distant Explosion]

1174
01:26:57,105 --> 01:27:01,105
- What's the fireworks?
-Knocking over one of Leo's clubs.

1175
01:27:01,310 --> 01:27:04,438
Son of a bitch
won't go belly up.

1176
01:27:04,513 --> 01:27:07,641
I'm sorry, kid.
I heard about your
little ride this morning.

1177
01:27:07,716 --> 01:27:09,650
Yeah, well,
sorry don't fix things.

1178
01:27:09,718 --> 01:27:13,552
We could just as easily
have missed Bernie's corpse,
and I'd be dead now.

1179
01:27:13,622 --> 01:27:17,388
I know, I know, but that don't mean
the Dane's up to anything.

1180
01:27:17,459 --> 01:27:21,293
So he hears a rumor
that Bernie ain't dead.
These stories pop up.

1181
01:27:21,363 --> 01:27:24,594
Any stories
about Bernie being alive
the Dane's made up himself.

1182
01:27:24,666 --> 01:27:28,534
You don't know that.
It don't make sense. Why would he?

1183
01:27:28,604 --> 01:27:31,038
There could be
a damn good reason...

1184
01:27:32,774 --> 01:27:35,607
if you got
a fixed fight coming up.

1185
01:27:37,913 --> 01:27:41,007
- Do you?
- Maybe.

1186
01:27:42,684 --> 01:27:46,684
Okay, yeah, sure.
Tomorrow night.
The fix is in. What of it?

1187
01:27:46,788 --> 01:27:49,052
- The Dane know about it?
- Yeah.

1188
01:27:52,928 --> 01:27:55,522
Okay, I get it.

1189
01:27:55,597 --> 01:27:58,532
If the Dane's been selling
you out on these fights
and means to again,

1190
01:27:58,600 --> 01:28:01,763
- he's gonna have to have somebody
else to point the finger at.
- Yeah, I get it.

1191
01:28:01,837 --> 01:28:04,271
With Bernie dead,
there ain't a hell of a lot
of people he can point to.

1192
01:28:04,339 --> 01:28:08,105
Yeah, the Dane sells me out,
makes pretend Bernie's still
doing it.

1193
01:28:08,176 --> 01:28:10,110
That's real pretty.

1194
01:28:10,178 --> 01:28:14,178
Bernie leaked the fix,
and you take the fall
for not killing him.

1195
01:28:16,385 --> 01:28:20,385
But I don't know.
Why would Eddie cross me
like that? Money?

1196
01:28:20,889 --> 01:28:23,119
Okay, everybody likes money,

1197
01:28:23,191 --> 01:28:26,388
but somehow it just
don't seem like him.

1198
01:28:26,461 --> 01:28:30,461
- And I know the Dane.
- Nobody knows anybody.
Not that well.

1199
01:28:31,066 --> 01:28:33,796
Money don't mean
that much to him.

1200
01:28:33,869 --> 01:28:36,099
Then it's not just
the money he's after.

1201
01:28:36,171 --> 01:28:39,902
- He's got a wart on his fanny.
- Huh?

1202
01:28:39,975 --> 01:28:43,536
A warton his fanny
giving him the fidgets.

1203
01:28:43,612 --> 01:28:46,046
Maybe he's sick of sitting
on the couch.

1204
01:28:46,114 --> 01:28:49,277
Maybe behind your desk
don't look like a bad place to move to.

1205
01:28:49,351 --> 01:28:51,819
Kid, you got a lip on you.

1206
01:28:53,121 --> 01:28:55,521
But youre honest.

1207
01:28:55,590 --> 01:28:59,185
That's something we can't
get enough of in this business.

1208
01:29:02,731 --> 01:29:06,189
I'll admit since last we jawed...

1209
01:29:06,268 --> 01:29:08,668
my stomach's
been seizing up on me.

1210
01:29:08,737 --> 01:29:11,706
If the Dane's saying
we should double-cross you--

1211
01:29:11,773 --> 01:29:15,773
You double-cross once,
where's it all end?

1212
01:29:16,111 --> 01:29:18,909
An interesting ethical question.

1213
01:29:19,982 --> 01:29:21,916
[ Sighs ]

1214
01:29:24,353 --> 01:29:27,584
I'll find the Dane,
talk to him,
straighten things out.

1215
01:29:27,656 --> 01:29:31,092
- Sure, talk to him.
Have a chat.
- I'll take care of it.

1216
01:29:31,159 --> 01:29:34,253
- Ask him if hes selling you out.
I'm sure he'll come clean.
- I'll take care of it.

1217
01:29:34,329 --> 01:29:37,890
- You're swimmin' in it.
- I said I'd take care of it!

1218
01:29:37,966 --> 01:29:41,060
[Plate Thuds, Rattles]

1219
01:29:47,376 --> 01:29:50,903
-Johnny.
- [ Grunts ]

1220
01:29:50,979 --> 01:29:54,979
My chin's hanging out
right alongside yours.

1221
01:29:56,952 --> 01:30:00,388
I'd worry a lot less if
I thought you were worrying enough.

1222
01:30:01,857 --> 01:30:04,792
[Gunshots, Explosions Continue]

1223
01:30:04,860 --> 01:30:06,794
But I am, kid.

1224
01:30:10,532 --> 01:30:12,466
Christ.

1225
01:30:13,702 --> 01:30:16,102
Running things.

1226
01:30:16,238 --> 01:30:18,138
[ Ringing ]

1227
01:30:26,381 --> 01:30:28,781
- Yeah?
- [ Bernie ]
I got your message.

1228
01:30:28,850 --> 01:30:32,013
Oh, Bernie. I had a dream
about you the other day.

1229
01:30:32,087 --> 01:30:35,614
- Yeah? A nightmare?
- On the contrary. Very sweet.

1230
01:30:35,690 --> 01:30:38,887
I dreamt you were
lying out at Miller's Crossing
with your face blown off.

1231
01:30:38,960 --> 01:30:42,452
- [ Chuckles ]
You get a kick out of that?
- I was in stitches.

1232
01:30:42,531 --> 01:30:45,398
- It's Mink, isn't it?
- I came back.
He wasn't happy to see me.

1233
01:30:45,467 --> 01:30:47,401
- Can you beat that?
- Some friend.

1234
01:30:47,469 --> 01:30:49,403
Yeah. You know what
a nervous boy he was.

1235
01:30:49,471 --> 01:30:53,305
I figured you're a friend,
maybe you could use
some insurance.

1236
01:30:53,375 --> 01:30:55,343
Did Mink have a .22?

1237
01:30:57,412 --> 01:31:00,438
-He already ditched it. Why?
- After he shot Rug?

1238
01:31:00,515 --> 01:31:03,678
- Yeah. How'd you know?
- Doesn't matter.

1239
01:31:03,752 --> 01:31:07,752
- I've been thinking about
our deal. You can stick it
in your ear.
- Huh?

1240
01:31:08,557 --> 01:31:11,993
You don't have anything
on me that I don't have on you,
so I'm calling your bluff.

1241
01:31:12,060 --> 01:31:14,324
- Wait a minute.
- I'm pulling out
tomorrow morning.

1242
01:31:14,396 --> 01:31:18,025
You only have to decide
whether or not I leave behind
a message for Caspar...

1243
01:31:18,100 --> 01:31:20,034
that youre still around.

1244
01:31:20,102 --> 01:31:22,536
If you want me to keep
my mouth shut, it's gonna
cost you some dough.

1245
01:31:22,604 --> 01:31:25,164
I figure a thousand bucks
is reasonable, so I want two.

1246
01:31:25,240 --> 01:31:28,471
- In a pig's eye!
- I'm going out. I'll be back
at 4:00 this morning.

1247
01:31:28,543 --> 01:31:31,478
If youre not here at my place,
4:00, with the dough,

1248
01:31:31,546 --> 01:31:34,845
- Caspar's gonna be
looking for you tomorrow.
- Wait, wait, wait!

1249
01:31:42,724 --> 01:31:46,182
- Got any money?
- No.

1250
01:31:47,562 --> 01:31:49,894
Okay.

1251
01:31:53,935 --> 01:31:56,028
[ Grunting ]

1252
01:31:59,441 --> 01:32:02,171
[Blows Landing]

1253
01:32:04,212 --> 01:32:06,146
Third race tonight.

1254
01:32:06,214 --> 01:32:10,014
By the finish, Tailor Made
had a view of the field.

1255
01:32:10,085 --> 01:32:12,576
You oughta lay off
the ponies, Tom.

1256
01:32:19,194 --> 01:32:21,128
Okay.

1257
01:32:22,864 --> 01:32:25,765
[ Groaning ]

1258
01:32:27,369 --> 01:32:30,930
Lazarre said he's sorry about this.
Its just getting out of hand.

1259
01:32:31,006 --> 01:32:32,940
Yeah.

1260
01:32:33,008 --> 01:32:34,942
He likes you, Tom.

1261
01:32:34,943 --> 01:32:36,943
He said we didn't have to
break anything.

1262
01:32:38,525 --> 01:32:40,686
It's okay.

1263
01:32:40,760 --> 01:32:43,354
Tell him there's
no hard feelings. Heh!

1264
01:32:43,429 --> 01:32:47,429
Christ, Tom...
he knows that.

1265
01:32:50,203 --> 01:32:52,364
Take care now.

1266
01:33:06,686 --> 01:33:08,654
- Tom Reagan.
- Yes, sir.

1267
01:33:08,721 --> 01:33:12,316
- Mr. Caspar's in the great room.
- Swell. Can you hold these?

1268
01:33:13,860 --> 01:33:15,885
Kid, what's the rumpus?

1269
01:33:15,962 --> 01:33:17,896
I got news.

1270
01:33:17,964 --> 01:33:21,127
Yeah. News at this end too.

1271
01:33:21,201 --> 01:33:23,635
My stomach's been
seizing up on me.

1272
01:33:23,703 --> 01:33:26,399
- Mink just told me that he--
- Eh?

1273
01:33:26,472 --> 01:33:29,999
- You talked to Mink?
- Yeah, on the phone.

1274
01:33:30,076 --> 01:33:33,204
The Dane wants you to think
that he's disappeared
so you can't talk to him,

1275
01:33:33,279 --> 01:33:36,339
- but he's been here in town.
- You sure it was Mink?

1276
01:33:36,416 --> 01:33:40,250
Yeah. See for yourself.
He's coming to my place,
4:00 this morning.

1277
01:33:40,320 --> 01:33:44,120
He's afraid of
a crossing with Dane.
He told me about the fix.

1278
01:33:44,190 --> 01:33:47,591
He says he'll sing for
a couple of grand skip money,
tell us everyone involved.

1279
01:33:47,660 --> 01:33:50,094
But youd better take care
of the Dane tonight.

1280
01:33:50,163 --> 01:33:53,030
Mink says he's
coming after us tonight.

1281
01:33:53,099 --> 01:33:55,033
[ Groans ]

1282
01:33:59,005 --> 01:34:01,565
Leo's holed up
at Whiskey Nick's dump.

1283
01:34:01,641 --> 01:34:03,575
What? How do you know?

1284
01:34:03,643 --> 01:34:06,771
[Dane]
That ain't all we know, smart guy.

1285
01:34:07,847 --> 01:34:11,146
Recognize your playmate?

1286
01:34:15,221 --> 01:34:18,054
You thought I'd quit, huh? Uh-uh.

1287
01:34:18,124 --> 01:34:21,059
I followed you
this afternoon,

1288
01:34:21,127 --> 01:34:24,756
and I wondered why Einstein
would wanna talk to a gorilla.

1289
01:34:24,831 --> 01:34:28,358
So I grabbed the gorilla,
and I beat it out of him.

1290
01:34:28,434 --> 01:34:32,029
You give me a big guy
every time. They break easy.
Not like you.

1291
01:34:32,105 --> 01:34:35,541
Is there a point,
or are you just brushing up
on your small talk?

1292
01:34:35,608 --> 01:34:39,100
I like that.
Cool under fire.

1293
01:34:40,179 --> 01:34:42,147
I'm impressed.

1294
01:34:43,816 --> 01:34:47,479
The gorilla didn't know
whose stiff we found,
but I can fill that in.

1295
01:34:47,553 --> 01:34:50,545
You killed Mink,
you son of a bitch!

1296
01:34:51,824 --> 01:34:55,225
It was Mink,
you son of a bitch.

1297
01:34:55,295 --> 01:34:59,295
It was Mink, and by God,
I'll hear you say it.

1298
01:35:00,233 --> 01:35:02,667
[ Tom ]
Is this how you told Drop
his story?

1299
01:35:04,937 --> 01:35:07,235
Come here, bum.

1300
01:35:11,010 --> 01:35:14,173
I am gonna send you
to a deep, dark place,

1301
01:35:14,247 --> 01:35:17,045
and I am gonna have fun doing it.

1302
01:35:17,116 --> 01:35:19,607
[ Gagging ]

1303
01:35:33,499 --> 01:35:35,467
Oof!.

1304
01:35:35,535 --> 01:35:39,535
You son of a bitch!
Son of a bitch!
You lousy son of a bitch!

1305
01:35:40,873 --> 01:35:44,639
If theres one thing
I can't stand,
it's a double-cross artist!

1306
01:35:44,711 --> 01:35:47,043
[DropScreaming]

1307
01:35:47,113 --> 01:35:50,139
I had a theory
about this son of a bitch!

1308
01:35:54,487 --> 01:35:58,487
Shut up, you lousy
son of a bitch, or I'll give you
something to holler about!

1309
01:35:59,459 --> 01:36:02,587
Johnny, it's okay.
The Dane made him do it.
It's not important.

1310
01:36:02,662 --> 01:36:06,223
Then make him shut it!

1311
01:36:06,299 --> 01:36:10,167
And we do the same to Mink
this very same night!

1312
01:36:10,236 --> 01:36:13,171
We can't double-cross Mink.
He wants to spill the whole setup.

1313
01:36:13,239 --> 01:36:16,868
- I've never let
a son of a bitch walk.
- You've never crossed anyone.

1314
01:36:16,943 --> 01:36:20,470
4:00, my place. Mink's
coming in on his own hook,
so I promised him the money.

1315
01:36:20,546 --> 01:36:24,546
- Don't make me out
to be a liar.
- [ Screaming ]

1316
01:36:28,321 --> 01:36:30,846
Look at this, kid.

1317
01:36:32,525 --> 01:36:35,460
Something I try to teach
all my boys.

1318
01:36:37,263 --> 01:36:39,857
[ Moaning ]

1319
01:36:45,037 --> 01:36:47,972
Always put one in the brain.

1320
01:36:58,184 --> 01:37:00,846
[Doorbell Jingles]

1321
01:37:09,929 --> 01:37:11,863
What's the rumpus?

1322
01:37:11,931 --> 01:37:15,458
I was just in the neighborhood
feeling a little daffy.

1323
01:37:15,535 --> 01:37:17,833
- What are you doing?
- Walking.

1324
01:37:17,904 --> 01:37:20,168
Don't let on more
than you have to.

1325
01:37:20,239 --> 01:37:22,173
In the rain.

1326
01:37:26,846 --> 01:37:28,780
Bernie's dead, isn't he?

1327
01:37:30,082 --> 01:37:33,176
- What makes you think that?
- That's no answer.

1328
01:37:37,924 --> 01:37:40,586
I can't tell you
anything yet.

1329
01:37:40,660 --> 01:37:43,595
No one really cares, do they?

1330
01:37:43,663 --> 01:37:47,663
- His friends
didn't really like him.
- He didn't like his friends.

1331
01:37:48,868 --> 01:37:52,099
You're someone to talk.
You're a son of a bitch, Tom.

1332
01:37:52,171 --> 01:37:55,106
You got me
to tell you where he was,
and then you killed him.

1333
01:37:56,375 --> 01:37:58,400
I want to know why.

1334
01:37:58,478 --> 01:38:02,244
- What was in it for you?
- Nothing for me.

1335
01:38:06,686 --> 01:38:10,383
Giving up Bernie was
the only way I could see to
straighten things out for Leo.

1336
01:38:12,425 --> 01:38:15,360
I thought you said
you didn't care about Leo.

1337
01:38:15,428 --> 01:38:19,091
I said we were through.
It's not the same thing.

1338
01:38:19,165 --> 01:38:21,725
I don't understand.
I don't care.

1339
01:38:21,801 --> 01:38:25,100
I don't care what reasons you had
or you thought you had.

1340
01:38:25,171 --> 01:38:27,696
He's still alive.

1341
01:38:29,842 --> 01:38:31,935
You expect me to believe you?

1342
01:38:37,216 --> 01:38:39,150
No.

1343
01:38:42,455 --> 01:38:45,549
That's you all over, Tom.

1344
01:38:45,625 --> 01:38:48,059
A lie and no heart.

1345
01:38:48,127 --> 01:38:50,061
[ Clicks ]

1346
01:39:06,045 --> 01:39:07,979
Oh--

1347
01:39:09,048 --> 01:39:10,982
[ Sobs ]

1348
01:39:15,454 --> 01:39:17,547
It isn't easy, is it, Verna?

1349
01:39:33,239 --> 01:39:37,141
[Johnny] But before
you even think about doing
that, you gotta towel down.

1350
01:39:37,209 --> 01:39:41,209
So you towel down first
with a hot towel,
as hot as you can stand.

1351
01:39:42,748 --> 01:39:45,308
Put the razor
in cold water, not hot,

1352
01:39:45,384 --> 01:39:48,114
because metal
does what in cold?

1353
01:39:48,187 --> 01:39:52,187
- I don't know, Johnny.
- That's why Im telling you!
It contracts.

1354
01:39:54,827 --> 01:39:58,695
That way you get
a first-class shave every time.

1355
01:39:58,764 --> 01:40:00,698
Okay, Johnny.

1356
01:40:03,336 --> 01:40:05,429
Ain't it the life though?

1357
01:40:09,041 --> 01:40:12,602
[ Tom ]
Hello, Sal. You can dangle.

1358
01:40:12,603 --> 01:40:16,603
Hello, Tom. You sure?
You don't look so hot.

1359
01:40:17,624 --> 01:40:19,455
I'm okay.

1360
01:40:22,095 --> 01:40:24,325
I'll drive him home.

1361
01:40:41,348 --> 01:40:43,282
[Streetcar Rumbling]

1362
01:40:46,886 --> 01:40:49,116
[Gunshots]

1363
01:41:16,850 --> 01:41:19,683
Mr. Reagan, there were shots.

1364
01:41:19,753 --> 01:41:22,688
Go down to the drug store
and call the police.

1365
01:41:24,391 --> 01:41:27,258
You'd better stay there
till the officers arrive.

1366
01:41:28,328 --> 01:41:30,387
Will my cats be all right?

1367
01:41:30,463 --> 01:41:32,522
Yeah, they'll be fine.

1368
01:42:08,368 --> 01:42:10,836
[Bernie Chuckling]

1369
01:42:24,284 --> 01:42:27,310
I get it. You set me up.

1370
01:42:27,387 --> 01:42:30,413
Anything to avoid
a little dirty work yourself, huh?

1371
01:42:32,492 --> 01:42:35,825
How'd you know he'd get it
and not me? Or didnt you care?

1372
01:42:35,895 --> 01:42:38,386
I figured you'd come early
looking for blood.

1373
01:42:38,465 --> 01:42:41,400
He wouldn't, so youd likely
have the drop on him.

1374
01:42:43,036 --> 01:42:47,036
You're right.
The chump never knew what hit him.

1375
01:42:47,307 --> 01:42:50,765
But if you knew
Id come to kill you,
how do you know I won't still?

1376
01:42:50,844 --> 01:42:53,836
Theres nothing init
for you now.

1377
01:42:53,913 --> 01:42:56,848
With him dead, you and me
got nothing on each other.

1378
01:42:57,817 --> 01:43:00,342
- Let me have the gun.
- Why?

1379
01:43:00,420 --> 01:43:02,854
Pin this on the Dane.

1380
01:43:02,922 --> 01:43:05,914
Neither of us want him
walking around after this.

1381
01:43:05,992 --> 01:43:09,758
The cops'll be Leo's now.
They wont care what
they hang the Dane for.

1382
01:43:09,829 --> 01:43:11,763
I guess that's true,

1383
01:43:11,831 --> 01:43:15,831
if you don't mind keeping
the gun that killed Caspar
and Mink.

1384
01:43:17,303 --> 01:43:19,703
Why did Mink
shoot Rug anyway?

1385
01:43:19,772 --> 01:43:21,763
I don't know.
It was just a mix-up.

1386
01:43:21,841 --> 01:43:24,309
Here.

1387
01:43:27,080 --> 01:43:30,846
- So youre gonna say
the Dane did this?
- Sure.

1388
01:43:30,917 --> 01:43:33,715
Mink thought Rug
was tailing him.

1389
01:43:33,786 --> 01:43:36,346
You know Mink. Hysterical.
Skin full of hop,
head full of boogey men.

1390
01:43:36,422 --> 01:43:40,422
Comes home crying one day,
saying he had to pop
one of the Dane's spies.

1391
01:43:41,060 --> 01:43:44,655
Rug was tailing Verna,
not Mink. Mink just
happened to be with her.

1392
01:43:44,731 --> 01:43:46,665
[Laughs]
Funny, ain't it?

1393
01:43:46,733 --> 01:43:49,964
Mink was terrified
the Dane'd find out me and him
were jungle dup together.

1394
01:43:50,036 --> 01:43:53,028
I bet you kept him
worried about that to
keep him under your thumb.

1395
01:43:53,106 --> 01:43:55,540
Yeah, so what?
Scratch, huh?

1396
01:43:55,608 --> 01:43:58,236
A little bonus.

1397
01:43:58,311 --> 01:44:01,712
- Why did Mink take Rug's hair?
- Beats me. The kid was dizzy.

1398
01:44:01,781 --> 01:44:05,781
Fifty-fifty on the dough?
Or maybe I should get more,
since I did the deed.

1399
01:44:08,488 --> 01:44:11,252
Okay, you keep it.
I want you to have it.

1400
01:44:18,031 --> 01:44:22,031
Bernie... we can't pin this
on the Dane.

1401
01:44:22,902 --> 01:44:26,902
- Why not?
- Because the Dane's already
dead halfway across town.

1402
01:44:28,808 --> 01:44:32,039
- What the hell
are you talking about?
- Eddie Dane is dead.

1403
01:44:32,111 --> 01:44:34,045
It's gotta be you.

1404
01:44:35,682 --> 01:44:38,048
I mean, it was your gun.

1405
01:44:38,117 --> 01:44:40,278
[ Chuckling ]

1406
01:44:40,353 --> 01:44:44,353
What is this?
What the hell are you talking about?

1407
01:44:44,624 --> 01:44:47,058
You--

1408
01:44:47,126 --> 01:44:50,721
You took my gun.
It's just your word against mine.

1409
01:44:52,098 --> 01:44:54,032
[ Clicks ]

1410
01:44:54,100 --> 01:44:56,227
Not necessarily.

1411
01:44:57,303 --> 01:44:59,498
Are you crazy?

1412
01:44:59,572 --> 01:45:02,939
We're square.
You said it yourself.
We got nothing on each other.

1413
01:45:03,009 --> 01:45:05,375
Yep.

1414
01:45:05,445 --> 01:45:09,445
So what's in it for you?
There's no angle.

1415
01:45:09,916 --> 01:45:12,851
You cant just shoot me
like that.

1416
01:45:16,289 --> 01:45:19,816
Jesus Christ,
it don't make sense.

1417
01:45:22,028 --> 01:45:23,962
Tommy--

1418
01:45:25,832 --> 01:45:28,426
Tommy!
[ Sobbing ]

1419
01:45:30,169 --> 01:45:32,103
Look in your heart.

1420
01:45:34,674 --> 01:45:37,438
- Look in your heart.
- What heart?

1421
01:46:14,180 --> 01:46:16,114
[ Dialing Phone ]

1422
01:46:22,455 --> 01:46:24,548
Tad? It's Tom.

1423
01:46:25,925 --> 01:46:28,917
Tell Lazarre
I got his money.

1424
01:46:28,995 --> 01:46:31,020
Yeah, all of it.

1425
01:46:31,097 --> 01:46:34,032
I wanna place a bet
on tonight's fight.

1426
01:46:39,038 --> 01:46:40,972
- They set you up downstairs?
- How's that?

1427
01:46:41,040 --> 01:46:43,167
A little hooch, whatever?

1428
01:46:43,242 --> 01:46:46,177
Thanks for coming, Tom.
Leo's real anxious to see you.

1429
01:46:46,245 --> 01:46:48,338
Yeah, I happened to be near.

1430
01:46:48,414 --> 01:46:50,575
[Indistinct Shouts]

1431
01:46:50,650 --> 01:46:53,881
Well, uh, actually this might
not be the best time.

1432
01:46:53,953 --> 01:46:56,888
- Who's he got in there?
- O'Doole and the mayor.

1433
01:46:56,956 --> 01:47:00,956
- I'll try again.
- They're planting the sheeny
tomorrow. You could stop by.

1434
01:47:04,430 --> 01:47:06,364
[ Mumbling Prayer]

1435
01:47:30,799 --> 01:47:34,394
- Big turnout.
- Drop dead.

1436
01:47:34,469 --> 01:47:36,562
She's under a lot of strain.

1437
01:47:36,638 --> 01:47:40,130
- Yeah, well, at least
she didn't hit me.
- [ Chuckles ]

1438
01:47:40,208 --> 01:47:43,575
Glad you came, Tommy.

1439
01:47:43,645 --> 01:47:47,411
- I guess, uh-- Huh?
- She's taking the car.

1440
01:47:52,120 --> 01:47:55,317
- I guess we're walkin'.
- Guess we are.

1441
01:48:00,228 --> 01:48:02,321
We're, uh--
We're getting married.

1442
01:48:05,133 --> 01:48:07,727
Congratulations.

1443
01:48:07,802 --> 01:48:11,802
Funny thing is, she asked me to
tie the knot. I guess you're
not supposed to say that.

1444
01:48:13,108 --> 01:48:15,975
- It doesn't matter.
Congratulations.
- Thanks.

1445
01:48:17,345 --> 01:48:20,280
Hell, Tom, why didnt you
tell me what you were up to?

1446
01:48:20,348 --> 01:48:22,782
I thought youd
really gone over.

1447
01:48:22,851 --> 01:48:26,446
Not that I didn't deserve it,
but you could've told me.

1448
01:48:26,521 --> 01:48:30,082
Telling you would only
have queered things if it--

1449
01:48:30,158 --> 01:48:33,127
There just wasn't any point.

1450
01:48:33,194 --> 01:48:35,128
I can see that.

1451
01:48:36,531 --> 01:48:39,625
It was a smart play all around.

1452
01:48:39,701 --> 01:48:42,761
I guess you know I'm grateful.

1453
01:48:42,837 --> 01:48:44,771
No need.

1454
01:48:46,508 --> 01:48:49,306
Heh!
I guess you picked
that fight with me...

1455
01:48:49,377 --> 01:48:52,813
just to check yourself
in with Caspar.

1456
01:48:52,881 --> 01:48:56,715
I don't know.
Do you always know
why you do things, Leo?

1457
01:48:56,785 --> 01:48:58,719
Sure I do.

1458
01:49:00,789 --> 01:49:03,553
- It was a smart play.
- Fine.

1459
01:49:06,795 --> 01:49:10,390
Jesus, Tom, I'd do anything
if youd work for me again.

1460
01:49:10,465 --> 01:49:13,764
I know I've made
some bonehead plays,
I know I can be pigheaded,

1461
01:49:13,835 --> 01:49:16,360
but, damn it, so can you.

1462
01:49:16,438 --> 01:49:20,438
I need you.
Things can be the way they were.

1463
01:49:21,042 --> 01:49:23,340
I know it.
I just know it.

1464
01:49:23,411 --> 01:49:27,411
As for you and Verna,
well, I understand.

1465
01:49:28,083 --> 01:49:30,847
You're both young.

1466
01:49:30,919 --> 01:49:33,217
Damn it, Tom, I forgive you.

1467
01:49:33,288 --> 01:49:35,722
I didn't ask for that,
and I don't want it.

1468
01:49:41,963 --> 01:49:43,897
Good-bye, Leo.

1469
01:49:55,000 --> 01:49:59,000
;y;